19ba4be0-819c-4065-a3dd-7729d6c53485	Data Portability	At the request of the individual, organisations are required to transmit the individual’s data that is in the organisation’s possession or under its control, to another organisation in a commonly used machine-readable format. \n\nExceptions may apply to the obligations above. For more information, please refer to Advisory Guidelines on Key Concepts in the Personal Data Protection Act.	56e2b62a-c393-4bcf-ae6d-1b8c4b0fa823	2025-08-25 17:06:59.287186+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	draft	\N	10	\N	lesson	\N	master
a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890	Introduction to the Personal Data Protection Act (PDPA)	Interactive data protection training focusing on creating a strong understanding of personal data, and how to protect and handle it.	\N	2025-07-09 18:02:16.051722+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	published	intro	10	\N	lesson	\N	master
af3d4820-1e57-4501-89f8-305aa9e7b9e9	HIB and Data Protection	This lesson covers what you need to know about data protection in relation to HIB.	56e2b62a-c393-4bcf-ae6d-1b8c4b0fa823	2025-09-11 05:38:07.870877+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	draft	\N	10	\N	lesson	\N	master
ad4e3c99-975a-427a-b680-03b774ec4317	Passphrase Best Practices	We all use passwords and know about using mixed cases, numbers, special characters, etc. when we create passwords. But are they really safe? This lesson covers the best practices of creating passwords that are secure, and not easily hackable. 	\N	2025-08-08 15:27:59.879887+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	published	node_1754667499326	4	56e2b62a-c393-4bcf-ae6d-1b8c4b0fa823	module	\N	master
3b34d10e-752a-47b2-a1e2-bd96272e75a8	Case Study - SP Group text / email scam	Over $12,000 lost to scammers claiming to be from SP Group	49a2e25a-8d73-4722-9440-eef9c9d4dc42	2025-11-12 07:00:13.025827+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	published	node_1762931377906	5	49a2e25a-8d73-4722-9440-eef9c9d4dc42	module	\N	master
9cfc3654-15eb-4d60-af87-83c9c8f2fa9f	Lock It Down - Protect What You Have	Most data breach investigation determine that lack of adequate security safeguards is the main causal factor.  Reasonable security arrangements must be implemented to protect the personal data that is in the organisation's possession to prevent unauthorised access, collection, use, disclosure or mitigate similar risks.	e5b43f83-f2cb-49c2-a036-558c2336d5a7	2025-11-12 10:13:27.132238+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	draft	\N	5	\N	lesson	\N	master
71b8e53b-4c95-4d67-aacf-0434f833fc47	Purpose LImitiation	Only collect, use or disclose personal data for the purposes that a reasonable person would consider appropriate under the given circumstances and for which the individual has given consent.\n\nAn organisation may not, as a condition of providing a product or service, require the individual to consent to the collection, use or disclosure of his or her personal data beyond what is reasonable to provide that product or service.	\N	2025-07-02 18:32:04.114242+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	published	node_1751487779564	5	\N	lesson	\N	master
26721096-1855-4d0b-835b-46025a7b4c3f	Quiz!	It's Quiz Time!  After 10 episodes, it's a good time to do a little quiz and see what you remember.  It'll help you and us be safe and cyber secure.  And of course, it's important for our clients and stakeholders.  It won't take more than 10 minutes!	\N	2025-07-08 18:23:40.888051+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	draft	\N	\N	\N	lesson	\N	master
ba58297d-d2cd-4f36-a80c-a0dcacb897de	Personal Data and You. Can you handle it? 	We all deal with people's personal data these days:  clients, colleagues, customers, voters, you name it.  We have to be careful.  Why did one company get fined over 850 million dollars?  Or a mayor gets fined 2 grand? It can be tricky:  what can we do, what can't we do, what do we have to do?  Let's take a look.	\N	2025-07-08 18:23:40.888051+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	published	node_1756415301542	10	\N	lesson	\N	master
db1709d0-cc53-424d-845e-47f77231e17f	Dont Hoard - Retention Bites	More is not always best. Done hoard or retain personal data longer than necessary. Cease retention of personal data or dispose of in a proper manner when it is no longer needed for any business or legal purpose.	e5b43f83-f2cb-49c2-a036-558c2336d5a7	2025-11-12 10:17:09.651067+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	draft	\N	5	\N	lesson	\N	master
4569c7a6-be9d-4740-8ca5-18f889c35d08	Less Is Best - Data Minimisation	The organisation should collect only what is absolutely necessary for the state purpose(s). More data equates to more risk of exposure and unauthorised access.	e5b43f83-f2cb-49c2-a036-558c2336d5a7	2025-11-12 13:13:56.806216+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	draft	\N	5	\N	lesson	\N	master
e8258a38-0f83-4d7d-967e-de642737e1cb	Overarching Obligations	The PDPA seems daunting but don't worry: this lesson explains your overarching obligations with regards to the act and walks you through critical terms you need to know, and sets the foundation of your knowledge of the PDPA.	\N	2025-07-08 18:23:40.888051+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	draft	node_1756586512109	10	\N	lesson	\N	master
57cde5ae-57f4-4a5d-a956-2368d7f851b8	HIB and Cybersecurity	This lesson covers what you need to know about cybersecurity in relation to HIB.	56e2b62a-c393-4bcf-ae6d-1b8c4b0fa823	2025-09-11 05:37:49.273498+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	published	\N	10	\N	lesson	\N	master
fc018c58-7bf8-4b54-ae01-79501989164a	Retention Limit	Cease retention of personal data or dispose of it in a proper manner when it is no longer needed for any business or legal purpose.	\N	2025-07-08 18:23:40.888051+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	draft	\N	10	\N	lesson	\N	master
207c4b5f-11b3-40e9-b062-103d1dae1263	Transfer Limitation	Transfer personal data to another country only according to the requirements prescribed under the regulations, to ensure that the standard of protection is comparable to the protection under the PDPA, unless exempted by the PDPC.	\N	2025-07-08 18:23:40.888051+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	published	node_1754256700672	10	\N	lesson	\N	master
84771ac6-e44a-4e3a-9bc0-acc0ccd6b4c8	Access and Correction	Upon request, organisations have to provide individuals with access to their personal data as well as information about how the data was used or disclosed within a year before the request.\n\nOrganisations are also required to correct any error or omission in an individual’s personal data as soon as practicable and send the corrected data to other organisations to which the personal data was disclosed (or to selected organisations that the individual has consented to), within a year before the correction is made. 	\N	2025-07-08 18:23:40.888051+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	draft	\N	10	\N	lesson	\N	master
696f4cfb-488c-4638-b33f-3f55fb10a822	HIB for Nursing Staff	Simplified lesson covering key HIB knowledge for Nursing Staff	56e2b62a-c393-4bcf-ae6d-1b8c4b0fa823	2025-09-11 05:41:21.957508+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	published	node_1757595841713	10	\N	lesson	\N	master
eccf0a0c-fb9e-47af-a9f8-2a0adeb9bd32	HIB for Nursing Staff - 2	This lesson focusses on managing passwords.	990a457c-eb6f-4202-8df6-f2c098c1b50c	2025-09-12 01:19:25.24387+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	published	node_1757640044013	10	\N	lesson	\N	master
09e15c67-cd0e-42cf-b68a-69541984f7b7	Notification	Notify individuals of the purposes for which your organisation is intending to collect, use or disclose their personal data.	\N	2025-07-08 18:23:40.888051+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	published	node_1754350416199	10	\N	lesson	\N	master
b9430ff6-c590-40a4-b620-ae26595b43be	Consent	Only collect, use or disclose personal data for purposes which an individual has given his/her consent to.\n\nAllow the individual to withdraw consent, with reasonable notice, and inform him/her of the likely consequences of withdrawal. Once consent is withdrawn, make sure that you cease to collect, use or disclose the individual’s personal data.	\N	2025-07-08 18:23:40.888051+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	published	\N	10	\N	lesson	\N	master
2b6a20d5-06af-4296-a0e6-3f859f399ea7	Simple mini node lesson	For generic testing purposes, including language translations.	56e2b62a-c393-4bcf-ae6d-1b8c4b0fa823	2025-08-17 03:37:59.728912+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	published	node_1755401924746	2	\N	lesson	\N	master
0d13dd7b-8552-4cfc-b24c-570faddede34	Data Breach Notification	In the event of a data breach, organisations must take steps to assess if it is notifiable. If the data breach likely results in significant harm to individuals, and/or are of significant scale, organisations are required to notify the PDPC and the affected individuals as soon as practicable.	56e2b62a-c393-4bcf-ae6d-1b8c4b0fa823	2025-08-25 17:05:20.220823+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	draft	\N	10	\N	lesson	\N	master
6e05305d-f774-4d57-bcb5-09be7800e062	Accuracy Obligation	Make reasonable effort to ensure that the personal data collected is accurate and complete, especially if it is likely to be used to make a decision that affects the individual or to be disclosed to another organisation.	\N	2025-07-08 18:23:40.888051+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	published	\N	10	990a457c-eb6f-4202-8df6-f2c098c1b50c	lesson	\N	master
825f3ae6-d593-4e25-9926-61542bcd8cd6	HIB Data Protection Cheat Sheet	This lesson covers the key information staff need to know in pictorial format.	56e2b62a-c393-4bcf-ae6d-1b8c4b0fa823	2025-09-11 16:45:32.64954+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	published	node_1757609140581	10	49a2e25a-8d73-4722-9440-eef9c9d4dc42	lesson	\N	master
76255dc9-84b9-4d63-b725-eb72136128f9	Accountability	The Accountability Obligation is an overarching responsibility that the organisation and each indvividual undertakes to protect the personal data that it has or is in control of. 	\N	2025-07-08 18:23:40.888051+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	published	node_1756625381826	5	990a457c-eb6f-4202-8df6-f2c098c1b50c	lesson	\N	master
1cda6a5b-6a8c-4556-b121-0e1eb4edac74	Protection	Reasonable security arrangements have to be made to protect the personal data in your organisation’s possession to prevent unauthorised access, collection, use, disclosure or similar risks.	\N	2025-07-08 18:23:40.888051+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	published	\N	10	990a457c-eb6f-4202-8df6-f2c098c1b50c	lesson	\N	master
4305695a-8ebb-4fe4-b79d-00389314cf20	Short Demo Quiz		56e2b62a-c393-4bcf-ae6d-1b8c4b0fa823	2025-09-20 05:15:52.564245+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	published	node_1762758762165	10	49a2e25a-8d73-4722-9440-eef9c9d4dc42	quiz	{"max_attempts": 10, "retry_policy": "limited", "trophy_config": {"trophy_name": "", "award_trophy": true, "trophy_description": ""}, "certificate_config": {"issuer": "Learning Platform", "certificate_name": "", "expires_after_days": null, "generate_certificate": true}, "passing_percentage": 70, "time_limit_minutes": null, "show_score_during_quiz": true}	master
4a933ccb-f446-4568-a685-4125abb87252	Your Data, Your Right - Access and Correction	The Data Subject has a right to request access to his/her personal data that is in the possession of or under the control of the organisation. The Data Subject also has the right to have any error or omission in his/her personal data corrected.  On receiving such requests, the organisation has to provide access as well as have the personal data corrected as soon as practicable.	e5b43f83-f2cb-49c2-a036-558c2336d5a7	2025-11-12 09:36:22.230254+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	draft	\N	5	e5b43f83-f2cb-49c2-a036-558c2336d5a7	lesson	\N	master
0fd716c1-142d-41f6-addb-6c2c77051f9e	Case Study - School Fees scam	Over $30,000 lost in new scam in Singapore involving requests for school fees by impersonators	49a2e25a-8d73-4722-9440-eef9c9d4dc42	2025-11-12 07:16:29.885635+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	published	node_1762931802103	5	49a2e25a-8d73-4722-9440-eef9c9d4dc42	module	\N	master
5569cc1a-1f8e-4e84-9237-66bcc3505747	Say Yes The Right Way - Consent Matters	It is important for any organisation, as a Data Controller, to get consent from the Data Subject, before collecting, using or disclosing personal data belonging to the Data Subject.  The organisation must allow the Data Subject to withdraw consent, and inform him/her of the likely consequences for withdrawing consent. Following consent withdrawal, the organisation must cease to collect, use or disclose the Data Subject's personal data.	e5b43f83-f2cb-49c2-a036-558c2336d5a7	2025-11-12 09:30:18.926665+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	draft	\N	5	e5b43f83-f2cb-49c2-a036-558c2336d5a7	lesson	\N	master
88783a2a-3b5f-4c1d-b87b-9fa20a644a08	No Surprises - Notify Before Handling Personal Data	The organisation must determine the purpose(s) clearly first and then notify the Data Subject of the purposes for which it intends to collect, use or disclose personal data.	e5b43f83-f2cb-49c2-a036-558c2336d5a7	2025-11-12 09:34:20.564046+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	draft	\N	5	e5b43f83-f2cb-49c2-a036-558c2336d5a7	lesson	\N	master
7a001c26-45dd-4fa5-a4b5-3e16992ae2d1	Check Twice - Accuracy Counts	The organisation must make reasonable effort to ensure the personal data in its possession or under its control is accurate and complete, especially if the personal data is likely to be used to make a decision that affects the individual or to be disclosed to another organisation.	e5b43f83-f2cb-49c2-a036-558c2336d5a7	2025-11-12 10:00:23.896713+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	draft	\N	5	\N	lesson	\N	master
5ec05932-5453-4698-ac3d-211f31f4af3c	Stay On Track - Purpose Only	The organisation is to only collect, use or disclose personal data for the purposes that it has stated, and for purposes that a reasonable Data Subject would consider appropriate. The organisation cannot compel a Data Subject to provide consent for collection, use of disclosure of his/her personal data to access the organisation's products and services.	e5b43f83-f2cb-49c2-a036-558c2336d5a7	2025-11-12 09:32:17.322908+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	draft	\N	5	e5b43f83-f2cb-49c2-a036-558c2336d5a7	lesson	\N	master
8501fccb-400b-465f-b677-2822cb58a06e	Cyber & Data Security Essentials - Overview	This lesson covers the fundamentals of cyber & data protection, covering the need for cyber security and data protection, how breaches occur and case studies.	56e2b62a-c393-4bcf-ae6d-1b8c4b0fa823	2025-11-03 02:59:58.247333+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	published	node_1762139574122	5	49a2e25a-8d73-4722-9440-eef9c9d4dc42	lesson	\N	master
a21b2fca-5229-4f76-9928-fcb597eabe05	Know the Difference - Personal Data vs Business Contact Information	Data Subjects (owners or suppliers of personal data) and Data Controllers (collectors, users or disclosers of personal data) are sometimes confused about personal data and business contact information (BCI). The PDPA distinguishes between the two terms and states clearly that the PDPA is applicable only to personal data.	e5b43f83-f2cb-49c2-a036-558c2336d5a7	2025-11-12 09:27:38.01772+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	draft	\N	5	\N	lesson	\N	master
0a03337d-abfb-42f4-8f53-b08438116785	Think Before You Ship - Transfer Safely	The organisation may transfer personal data to another country only according to the requirements in the PDPA, to ensure that standards of protection in the recipient country is comparable to the protection under the PDPA. An exemption may be given by the PDPC.	e5b43f83-f2cb-49c2-a036-558c2336d5a7	2025-11-12 10:19:37.946226+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	draft	\N	5	\N	lesson	\N	master
09641deb-c60c-4644-ad5f-974568d4adc1	Act Fast - Breach Notification	If there is a data breach, the organisation must take steps to assess if it is notifiable. If the data breach is likely to result in significant harm to Data Subjects and/or are of significant scale, the organisation is required to notify the PDPC and the affected Data Subject as soon as is practicable.	e5b43f83-f2cb-49c2-a036-558c2336d5a7	2025-11-12 10:25:23.562874+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	draft	\N	5	\N	lesson	\N	master
c93d1fcc-2dbe-4acd-91f2-6fa48ac97645	Own It - Accountability Starts With You	The organisation must implement measure to ensure it meets its obligations under the PDPA such as making information about your data protection policies, practices and complaints process available upon request and designating a data protection officer (DPO) and making the business contact information available to the public.	e5b43f83-f2cb-49c2-a036-558c2336d5a7	2025-11-12 10:28:24.423568+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	draft	\N	5	\N	lesson	\N	master
3db2e2a8-e414-4730-bef8-d23405d3b83c	Move It Right - Data Portability Explained	At the request of the Data Subject, the organisation is required to transmit the Data Subject's data that is in the organisation’s possession or under its control, to another organisation in a commonly used machine-readable format. 	e5b43f83-f2cb-49c2-a036-558c2336d5a7	2025-11-12 13:11:33.304741+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	draft	\N	5	\N	lesson	\N	master
bcee725b-ca0e-4ff1-8d9e-ac9b40b71471	Choose Wisely - Vendor Management	Assess all vendors using a structure methodology, risk score them where necessary and determine their suitability to meet the organisation's cybersecurity and data protection needs. The organisation, as a data controller, is also accountable for the vendor's lapses.	e5b43f83-f2cb-49c2-a036-558c2336d5a7	2025-11-12 13:16:12.590473+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	draft	\N	5	\N	lesson	\N	master
fb20af5f-bccd-42dd-8dd8-60a3df6302f3	Don't Call Me - Respect The DNC	The organisation is to ensure that it complies with Do Not Call (DNC) provisions before initiating marketing calls to potential customers	e5b43f83-f2cb-49c2-a036-558c2336d5a7	2025-11-12 13:18:16.08737+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	draft	\N	5	\N	lesson	\N	master
c49ade42-51ea-4a13-97bb-34fe61297bb7	Lock It Right - Passphrase Power	Learn how strong passphrases and multi-factor authentication (MFA) protect accounts from hackers. Learn how to determine if your chosen passphrase(s) are strong enough to resist hacking.	e5b43f83-f2cb-49c2-a036-558c2336d5a7	2025-11-12 13:20:00.753096+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	draft	\N	5	\N	lesson	\N	master
b7a6accb-772a-4140-951d-a6e79d15cd8e	Spot The Bait - Dont Get Hooked	Understanding phishing and social engineering tactics that trick users into giving away sensitive data. Don't become a victim.	e5b43f83-f2cb-49c2-a036-558c2336d5a7	2025-11-12 13:21:16.780701+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	draft	\N	5	\N	lesson	\N	master
cb769b3f-9317-47f1-b837-d9e1fe0a2f5e	Think Before You Click - Email & Messaging Safety	Learn and live safe practices for handling emails, attachments and chat messages, to mitigate risk of unauthorised data leakages.	e5b43f83-f2cb-49c2-a036-558c2336d5a7	2025-11-12 13:23:02.771848+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	draft	\N	5	\N	lesson	\N	master
d77a9ffd-4278-4bdf-b0fb-30b1139d981d	Patch It Up - Stay Secure	Learn why software updates and device security are critical to prevent the organisation's digital environment from being attacked.	e5b43f83-f2cb-49c2-a036-558c2336d5a7	2025-11-12 13:24:20.390532+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	draft	\N	5	\N	lesson	\N	master
7ee8827d-176a-4864-94e6-03baf88e8685	Speak Up Fast - Report Incidents Early	Know how and why to report security incidents promptly to prevent escalation.  Realise that speed saves systems and data.	e5b43f83-f2cb-49c2-a036-558c2336d5a7	2025-11-12 13:26:40.006941+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	draft	\N	5	\N	lesson	\N	master
5257dcb1-1fa5-4ce7-b9fe-106e5d3bdbf0	Guard The Gold - Protect Sensitive Data Always	Explore how to handle confidential data securely across devices and platforms. Encrypt, store safely, and avoid sharing sensitive data on unsecured channels.	e5b43f83-f2cb-49c2-a036-558c2336d5a7	2025-11-12 13:25:12.353272+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	draft	\N	5	e5b43f83-f2cb-49c2-a036-558c2336d5a7	lesson	\N	master
76244897-3d71-4d9a-9b00-fe2b1b95ffe3	S3 test		56e2b62a-c393-4bcf-ae6d-1b8c4b0fa823	2025-11-13 03:56:18.233926+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	draft	\N	5	\N	lesson	\N	master
