node_1756419487917	ba58297d-d2cd-4f36-a80c-a0dcacb897de	question	Sarah attended a business event. At the registration counter, she gave her business card. The business card had her personal mobile number. Is the personal mobile number considered personal data or Business Contact Information in this scenario?	\N	\N	\N	2025-08-28 22:25:50.497559+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	943	1319	\N	f	1	1	\N	6aa0b805ec58d180d72d4662d7ac2dc1a6de0a04a2e395584f02673111b61cef	master
node_1757593807679	fcbb989f-565d-4f87-8a65-a419ba7b69e1	prompt	Well, that's why Singapore introduced the Health Information Bill (HIB).\nThe HIB explains clearly what you must do to prevent data breach incidents.	\N	\N	\N	2025-09-11 12:49:07.999585+00	2025-11-15 09:36:21.867474+00	445	103	node_1757593982551	\N	\N	\N	\N	b00b76f5903244ffd1ae0626277aeecf798cd5e199836cf010dcd3510e8f3fb7	master
